  ;;
  ;; ── Design notes ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ;;
  (text "DISPLAY INTERFACE NOTES:\n\nSPI2 (LCD_CAM peripheral) — 4-wire SPI:\n  GPIO17 = LCD_CLK  (SPI2 clock, 80MHz max)\n  GPIO18 = LCD_MOSI (SPI2 MOSI, pixel data out)\n  GPIO11 = LCD_CS   (SPI2 CS, active LOW)\n  GPIO16 = LCD_DC   (Data=HIGH, Command=LOW)\n  No MISO needed — display is write-only\n\nGT911 CAPACITIVE TOUCH:\n  I2C address: 0x5D (INT pulled HIGH before RST released)\n              or 0x14 (INT pulled LOW before RST released)\n  Use 0x5D as default — pull INT HIGH during RST sequence in firmware\n  Shared I2C bus with ES8388 (addresses 0x10/0x11) — no conflict\n  INT (GPIO44) is input-only — correct for interrupt-driven touch\n  RST (GPIO43) shared with LCD_RST — both reset together at power-on\n\nSHARED RST SEQUENCE:\n  1. Assert RST LOW (GPIO43 LOW)\n  2. Wait 10ms\n  3. Deassert RST HIGH (GPIO43 HIGH)\n  4. Wait 100ms for display init\n  5. GT911 is also ready by this point\n  This is safe — GT911 tolerates extended reset assertion\n\nBACKLIGHT:\n  GPIO46 = PWM via LEDC peripheral (any frequency 1Hz–40MHz)\n  Typical: 5kHz, 8-bit duty cycle for flicker-free dimming\n  +5V_BL rail: direct from +5V_EXT, max 200mA\n  C21 (10µF) provides local bulk for LED inrush\n\nIPC-2221B LAYOUT RULES FOR THIS SHEET:\n  SPI2 traces (CLK, MOSI, CS, DC) must have unbroken GND plane beneath\n  Keep SPI2 traces away from HUB75 CLK and LAT (both switching at 20MHz+)\n  FPC pads: ENIG finish required. IPC-7351C Level B land pattern.\n  Stencil aperture: 80% for 0.5mm FPC pads\n  ESD protection TVS on LCD_CLK and LCD_MOSI recommended for production"
    (at 30 125 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top)))
)
